Additionally, the paper makes use of a connection between minimum ranks of sign pattern matrices and the stretchability problem for pseudolines arrangements, which is a problem in computational geometry. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of algorithms and polynomial time complexity, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also deals with combinatorial optimization, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions graph theory and linear algebra, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
